cs.CR, cs.DB, cs.CY, cs.LG, cs.DC 

The paper discusses the privacy and security concerns in blockchain technology and proposes the integration of differential privacy to overcome these issues. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses the use of blockchain as a distributed ledger for data tracking and storage, which falls under the category of cs.DB (Databases). The paper also discusses the potential future applications of blockchain technology, which could fall under the categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper discusses the use of peer-to-peer networks and cryptographic hash functions, which could fall under the category of cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
